WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:03.265
Welcome to the James River Church Podcast.

00:03.285 --> 00:06.990
You're about to hear another inspirational message from Pastor John Lindell.

00:07.010 --> 00:08.852
Lead pastor at James River Church.

00:09.172 --> 00:13.137
It's our prayer that this message is an encouragement and blessing to your life.

00:14.459 --> 00:17.823
I want to talk to you about a hunger for God.

00:17.883 --> 00:26.994
Not a hunger for food that's controlled by a hormone in your stomach called ghrelin.

00:27.586 --> 00:36.795
And ghrelin, you may not have heard of it, but there are two ends or hormones in your stomach that control your digestion, insulin, and ghrelin.

00:37.136 --> 00:38.337
Ghrelin is really important.

00:38.377 --> 00:39.398
It does five things for it.

00:39.438 --> 00:41.840
It signals the brain to increase your appetite.

00:41.861 --> 00:44.143
You wouldn't be hungry if you didn't have ghrelin.

00:44.944 --> 00:48.467
It stimulates your pituitary gland to release growth hormones.

00:49.648 --> 00:55.154
Third, it stimulates your digestive system to move food from your stomach through your intestinal tract.

00:55.746 --> 01:03.274
fourth, it helps your body control insulin release, and fifth, it plays a role in cardiovascular health.

01:04.775 --> 01:14.205
I want to talk to you about having a hunger for God, because in the same way that ghrelin does things for our body physiologically, a hunger for God will do things for you spiritually.

01:16.787 --> 01:23.474
It's important that you and I have a hunger for the things of God

01:24.066 --> 01:28.971
because it does take us deeper into our walk with the Lord.

01:30.493 --> 01:33.496
Proverbs 27 and verse seven, this is via text for tonight.

01:33.837 --> 01:39.883
A person who is full refuses honey, but even bitter food tastes sweet to the hungry.

01:41.765 --> 01:46.331
The NIV puts it this way, he who is full loaves honey.

01:47.071 --> 01:49.194
It's interesting that word loaves means tramples.

01:50.415 --> 01:53.138
So what you have is when a person is full

01:53.442 --> 02:10.909
Even something that's good, even something that's good for them, even something that would be universally thought of as good, is all of the sudden trampled under the foot, is criticized, is not wanted, is not desired.

02:10.929 --> 02:22.226
And I wanna suggest to you that when people lose their spiritual hunger for God, the good things in their life are unappreciated.

02:23.586 --> 02:26.770
The good things God wants to do are unappreciated.

02:27.210 --> 02:30.835
I want to give you just quickly three principles on spiritual hunger.

02:31.155 --> 02:35.620
First of all, a lack of spiritual hunger will keep us from receiving.

02:36.281 --> 02:41.167
In Proverbs 27 and verse 7, he who is full loath's honey.

02:42.248 --> 02:47.154
The spiritual fullness that the writer of Proverbs is talking about, he's using

02:47.234 --> 02:49.678
honey and something that tastes bitter.

02:49.718 --> 02:53.884
He's using all of that as a metaphor for our spiritual life.

02:54.284 --> 03:01.455
And he isn't talking about what he's talking about here is not a fullness of God, but full of other things.

03:03.658 --> 03:06.642
I mean, it's being full of opinions.

03:08.104 --> 03:12.050
There are some people who aren't hungry for God because they're so full of their own opinions.

03:12.994 --> 03:17.399
There are some people who aren't hungry for God because they're so full of their own preferences.

03:18.360 --> 03:22.945
There are some people who are not full of God because they're full of worldliness.

03:25.067 --> 03:36.280
They're more worried about their status, they're more worried about their income, they're more worried about their own self-accomplishment or sensuality or greed.

03:37.881 --> 03:42.066
Some people are too full of other things

03:42.274 --> 03:43.075
for God to fill them.

03:45.238 --> 03:47.942
My question to you is, are you hungry for God tonight?

03:49.524 --> 03:59.038
How does it happen that a person could actually find themselves in a place where the presence of God is so real and not be hungry for it?

04:01.281 --> 04:04.626
Be looking at their watch to wonder how much longer are we going to do this?

04:08.802 --> 04:11.950
He's saying, well, you know, I hope they do this.

04:12.010 --> 04:12.832
I hope they do that.

04:13.052 --> 04:18.506
You see, they're full of their own thoughts, their own ideas, their own opinions.

04:18.526 --> 04:25.042
One of the ways that happens is through familiarity, what happens, we get so used to it, we no longer are in awe of it.

04:27.778 --> 04:43.023
One of the things I pray for myself is, God, give me a breathless awe of what you're doing in this place that I might always be amazed of the hand of God that rests on these people and on this church and its ministry.

04:45.307 --> 04:54.802
When what is extraordinary becomes ordinary in our sight, it's a sign that something's wrong with our spiritual hunger.

04:56.578 --> 04:58.040
Now there's a consumer mindset.

04:58.100 --> 05:06.291
I mean, what's in it for me where church becomes about us and it's what we want, what we like, what we need, how we feel.

05:08.294 --> 05:20.690
If that's what drives you when you come here, rather than I've come into this place and God is going to come down on the praise of his people, he will be enthroned, he will be here and I'm here to worship him.

05:20.951 --> 05:26.418
When we have any other agenda, primarily than that, it's because we're not hungry.

05:28.674 --> 05:32.719
hidden sin will always cripple a hunger for God.

05:34.501 --> 05:36.443
Pride will cripple a hunger for God.

05:36.703 --> 05:38.646
It's pride that says, I'm fine.

05:38.946 --> 05:40.728
It's pride that says, I know it all.

05:40.968 --> 05:44.552
It's pride that says there's nothing new that I need to learn.

05:44.793 --> 05:46.855
There's nothing new I need to experience.

05:46.955 --> 05:48.177
I've experienced it all.

05:48.217 --> 05:49.098
I've seen it all.

05:49.478 --> 05:52.021
And if it's something I haven't seen, I don't want it.

05:52.061 --> 05:52.882
That's pride.

05:54.978 --> 06:00.706
The problem with being full is that instead of entering into a move of God, we begin to evaluate the move of God.

06:02.869 --> 06:04.652
We begin actually to loathe it.

06:06.314 --> 06:06.975
It's too long.

06:07.696 --> 06:08.417
It's too loud.

06:08.898 --> 06:09.899
It's too emotional.

06:10.520 --> 06:11.521
It's not my style.

06:12.122 --> 06:13.044
I'm not comfortable.

06:13.064 --> 06:15.928
I like so-and-so's preaching better.

06:16.569 --> 06:18.391
We sing too many new songs.

06:18.411 --> 06:23.218
When those things start coming out, you got to see that as a warning and say, whoops,

06:23.970 --> 06:31.020
Something's wrong here, and the problem isn't with what's happening on the platform, it's what's happening in the heart.

06:32.883 --> 06:40.113
Because suddenly it's become about you, instead of about what God is doing.

06:42.015 --> 06:48.124
When you're full, you don't come to the table to eat, you come to the table to evaluate the menu.

06:51.409 --> 06:52.370
So ask yourself,

06:52.482 --> 06:59.219
Do I come to the services asking what's in it for me or do I come to the services asking God, what do you want to do in me?

07:00.442 --> 07:01.444
Listen, can I be honest with you?

07:01.524 --> 07:03.289
I'm not here to analyze the move of God.

07:03.630 --> 07:05.554
I'm here to be wrecked by a move of God.

07:06.296 --> 07:07.559
I mean, that's the whole thing.

07:08.201 --> 07:10.226
You say, well, give me a chapter in verse.

07:10.402 --> 07:17.369
When Isaiah saw the Lord, and he was high and lifted up, and his train filled the temple, and we just sang about that.

07:17.649 --> 07:18.510
What did he say?

07:18.810 --> 07:19.851
What was me?

07:20.131 --> 07:21.292
I'm undone.

07:21.733 --> 07:27.038
I'm a wreck.

07:27.058 --> 07:40.370
If God comes into place, and we don't eventually come to that moment where we're so overwhelmed by his power and his presence, and at the same time so hungry for more, something is wrong.

07:43.746 --> 07:46.530
I'm here to be rearranged by a move of God.

07:47.791 --> 07:50.014
I'm here to say whatever you want in my life, God.

07:51.015 --> 07:57.764
I'm here to say, God, it doesn't matter what I think, what matters is what you want to do.

07:58.525 --> 08:03.111
It's your house, it's your place, and we've come to worship you.

08:05.474 --> 08:12.082
You see, when a person doesn't have a spiritual hunger, what they do have is a spirit of control.

08:15.938 --> 08:20.183
Rather than yielding to the Lord, they want to control things.

08:20.824 --> 08:24.728
And usually it veers toward their comfort, their preference, those kind of things.

08:25.309 --> 08:29.654
Listen, hunger is so important because without it, you can't receive.

08:30.996 --> 08:33.198
Number two, hunger changes your taste.

08:34.540 --> 08:35.901
Look at this, that's so interesting.

08:35.941 --> 08:38.124
A person who is full refuses honey.

08:39.105 --> 08:40.226
But even bitter food.

08:41.989 --> 08:43.250
How many like bitter food?

08:44.834 --> 08:46.836
Anybody, you're like, I love bitter food.

08:47.497 --> 08:49.539
If you're hungry, you will love it.

08:50.880 --> 08:54.303
If you haven't eaten for seven days, bitter food's gonna be your best friend.

08:54.864 --> 08:57.466
You're like, man, I've never had anything so good in all my life.

08:57.767 --> 09:02.671
That sort of thing, but even bitter food tastes sweet to the hungry.

09:03.352 --> 09:07.756
You see, hunger changes what you and I are willing to embrace.

09:09.678 --> 09:11.740
A hungry person can receive.

09:12.621 --> 09:13.682
They can receive

09:13.858 --> 09:18.444
correction that stings but heals.

09:18.464 --> 09:23.831
They can receive conviction that's uncomfortable but cleanses.

09:23.851 --> 09:31.722
They can receive confrontation that's a little bit uncomfortable but causes them to grow.

09:33.064 --> 09:38.491
Because a hungry person is not looking for God to cater to them, they want God to transform them.

09:40.574 --> 09:43.858
You will know if you're hungry by what you want God to do for you.

09:45.602 --> 09:48.466
If you want God to cater to you, you're not hungry.

09:49.587 --> 09:50.128
You're selfish.

09:51.851 --> 09:52.692
This is a hard word.

09:54.815 --> 09:58.159
I mean, if that's all you came for is what you could get, it's all about you.

09:58.219 --> 10:02.525
And nothing we would ever do will in the long-term please you.

10:04.388 --> 10:06.831
But to the hungry person every day is a feast.

10:09.895 --> 10:12.239
I can't remember where that is in the Bible, but it's in the Bible.

10:12.739 --> 10:14.802
To the person who's hungry every day is a feast.

10:16.002 --> 10:21.228
Everything is when you're hungry, it's like, wow, I can't believe I get to be a part of this.

10:21.649 --> 10:30.719
When you're hungry, you just wanna see God do more in you so he can do more to you so that you can glorify him.

10:30.739 --> 10:37.767
You're just saying, God, whatever you want me to do, however you wanna use me, it's not about what I want to do, it's about what you want me to do.

10:37.847 --> 10:43.474
And I'm just here at your disposal, God, I'm hungry for you.

10:45.858 --> 10:52.206
Bitter means challenging, but even bitter food tastes sweet to the hungry.

10:53.447 --> 10:58.113
So bitter could be challenging, stretching, sanctifying, humbling.

10:58.153 --> 11:02.578
Because when God's working in a place, let me just assure you of this.

11:02.958 --> 11:04.560
And I don't care where you've come from.

11:04.941 --> 11:12.850
When God is working in a place, He will do things to offend your mind so that you can see your heart.

11:15.746 --> 11:17.428
He'll do things you don't understand.

11:18.730 --> 11:20.352
He'll do things you can't explain.

11:22.054 --> 11:29.224
Because he wants to find out if, because if you gotta have an explanation for everything, you gotta understand everything, then you're God.

11:32.108 --> 11:45.746
When you're in the presence of God, you come to the end of yourself and you come to the beginning of him and he is a mysterious, awesome God who you and I

11:45.922 --> 11:47.544
cannot completely understand.

11:47.604 --> 11:51.529
His ways, his works are too wonderful because his ways are higher than our ways.

11:54.392 --> 12:08.689
And so when you and I come into the place where God is moving, we have to be careful that we aren't offended by what God does.

12:09.610 --> 12:13.234
It's in Matthew chapter 11,

12:13.506 --> 12:24.176
John had heard in prison about the works of Jesus Christ, Matthew chapter two, or 11 verse two, excuse me, he sent two of his disciples and said to him, are you one coming or do we look for another?

12:24.616 --> 12:29.381
Jesus answered and said to them, go and tell John the things which you hear and see.

12:29.441 --> 12:39.170
The blind see, the lame walk, the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised up and the poor have the gospel preached to them.

12:39.190 --> 12:43.154
Then Jesus says this, and blessed is he,

12:43.362 --> 12:45.885
who is not offended because of me.

12:47.086 --> 12:49.509
Think of how many people were offended by Jesus' ministry.

12:52.032 --> 12:54.655
So easy to get offended by what we don't understand.

12:56.257 --> 13:01.504
Why this person got healed, this person didn't, or especially hard if you're the person who didn't get healed.

13:04.027 --> 13:05.949
Why this happened or why that happened?

13:06.329 --> 13:10.194
I'm not talking about unbiblical chaos

13:10.434 --> 13:16.080
But I am telling you that in a move of God, there's a lot of things that happen that leave people with questions.

13:16.320 --> 13:20.764
On the day of Pentecost, they were amazed and perplexed and confused.

13:21.025 --> 13:26.771
The Bible uses all those words in from verse six to 12 in Acts chapter two.

13:29.934 --> 13:38.162
If any of us think we can come into the presence of God and understand everything that's happening in the presence of God, we're being foolish and spiritually unwise.

13:40.418 --> 13:48.830
And what I'm saying is the posture, the appropriate posture is to say, God, I'm just so hungry for you that I want everything you wanna do in my life.

13:49.812 --> 13:52.015
And I may not understand it even as you do it.

13:55.400 --> 14:02.230
I know this a few years back, there was this season where every day I wept, I wept so much that my voice, I lost my voice.

14:02.691 --> 14:07.378
People were saying, you better go through an ear nose throat doctor because you're gonna wreck your voice.

14:07.618 --> 14:09.360
And they were like, what's happening?

14:09.380 --> 14:11.684
And I said, it's from weeping, that's what it's wrong.

14:14.147 --> 14:15.208
I didn't understand it.

14:15.809 --> 14:17.512
At one point, I thought, maybe I'm going crazy.

14:17.532 --> 14:21.577
I mean, you're kind of like, this is, this is, I just would begin to weep.

14:23.620 --> 14:27.505
And it would go for hours in the presence of the Lord.

14:28.427 --> 14:32.232
I like back on it now, I have a much better understanding now than I had then.

14:32.292 --> 14:36.818
But God was doing a work in me that he wanted to do.

14:39.490 --> 14:45.696
There wasn't what I would have preferred, but was what I needed nonetheless.

14:49.620 --> 14:53.924
I'm just simply saying, I look back on it now and it'll be something I'll never forget for the rest of my life.

14:55.546 --> 14:59.570
And it's not the benchmark for God working in my life.

14:59.950 --> 15:02.452
It's just another experience of God working in my life.

15:04.674 --> 15:08.338
And I stand here tonight and I say, God, whatever you want to do, whatever it is,

15:09.538 --> 15:10.399
I'm in, I'm on.

15:12.322 --> 15:15.207
I'm hungry for more of you.

15:15.227 --> 15:18.192
I want more of you.

15:18.252 --> 15:32.014
Ask yourself, have you found yourself offended by things that make you uncomfortable?

15:32.034 --> 15:34.738
Listen, I'm not talking

15:35.490 --> 15:39.574
What we've experienced and done is very much within the confines of Scripture.

15:39.914 --> 15:40.795
Let's be clear on that.

15:43.818 --> 15:47.761
But it is outside the bounds of most people's tradition.

15:50.404 --> 15:52.386
And for many people outside their comfort zone.

15:54.087 --> 15:54.888
And that's okay.

15:57.230 --> 16:02.936
Ask yourself, have you found yourself offended because others around you are more passionate about God than you are?

16:04.257 --> 16:05.458
If it offends you,

16:05.634 --> 16:09.780
that people are passionately worshiping God, that problem isn't theirs, it's yours.

16:12.804 --> 16:20.554
You should be delighted that people are so passionate and hungry for him that they've lost theirself in him.

16:22.417 --> 16:23.778
That's a glorious thing.

16:23.798 --> 16:31.849
It is why there's a freedom in our worship today that we hadn't had for 30 years.

16:34.032 --> 16:35.314
And I will always take that.

16:36.866 --> 16:46.116
Ask yourself, have you found yourself offended because your church preferences and traditions have become more important than wanting all that God has.

16:46.256 --> 16:51.162
So, you know, like, well, I don't think it should be done that to this, this, this, your opinion, your preferences.

16:51.522 --> 17:00.993
I'm just simply saying, if you find yourself offended by what God is doing, invariably it's because there isn't a hunger for God.

17:01.493 --> 17:02.995
That's what this scripture is.

17:03.015 --> 17:05.778
We go back to Proverbs 27 and verse seven.

17:05.858 --> 17:08.222
A person who is full refuses honey, he loads honey.

17:08.462 --> 17:10.705
He doesn't want anything to do with honey, doesn't need honey.

17:11.687 --> 17:24.305
Jesus said this, and Luke, I think it's chapter five and verse 38 or 37, and no one having drunk the old wine wants the new.

17:26.048 --> 17:28.592
The old they say is good enough.

17:30.975 --> 17:33.139
You have to be careful when you're hungry, you want the new wine.

17:34.461 --> 17:35.442
So Jesus is saying,

17:36.290 --> 17:37.492
He was new wine.

17:38.913 --> 17:50.708
I'm just simply saying how committed to pursuing God are you and how willing are you to say God have your way in my life, whatever that looks like and whatever that means.

17:52.691 --> 17:55.975
Hunger is third intensified by pursuit.

17:55.995 --> 17:57.016
Musicians you can come.

17:57.977 --> 18:04.946
A person who is full refuses honey, but even bitter food tastes sweet to the hungry.

18:05.122 --> 18:10.089
to the one who's pursuing it, Psalm 34 verse eight says, taste and seed that the Lord is good.

18:11.711 --> 18:16.698
In other words, spiritual hunger isn't a personality trait.

18:19.422 --> 18:24.289
You can't look at people who obviously are spiritually hungry and say, well, that's just how they roll.

18:24.649 --> 18:26.932
No, it's not a personality trait, it's a pursuit.

18:29.135 --> 18:34.002
It's a decision that they made to say

18:34.242 --> 18:35.603
I'm gonna go after God.

18:36.785 --> 18:42.451
Now I'm just gonna tell you, for most of my ministry, I live the fairly reserved life.

18:43.452 --> 18:47.777
I'm very committed to the Lord in one sense, but very reserved in the other.

18:47.797 --> 19:03.954
And the problem is, when reservation that can quickly become about your own dignity and your own image becomes more important than what God wants to do in your life, then you will miss things God would have done in your life

19:04.034 --> 19:05.195
that would have benefited you.

19:09.160 --> 19:19.633
And so I'm simply saying, the better thing is to say, I don't ever wanna be in a place where I'm turning up my nose at what's good.

19:21.295 --> 19:21.916
Honey's good.

19:24.399 --> 19:26.001
Taste and see the Lord is good.

19:27.363 --> 19:27.884
He's good.

19:29.486 --> 19:33.010
And I don't ever wanna be in a place where I'm saying, well, you know, that may be

19:33.122 --> 19:34.584
But this is where I want to be.

19:35.285 --> 19:37.167
Because then that means I've lost my hunger.

19:37.187 --> 19:40.732
When I've lost my spiritual hunger, then spiritual death has begun to set in.

19:43.196 --> 19:48.883
Hungry people show up early because they're eager to receive and want to prepare themselves to receive.

19:49.244 --> 19:56.133
And listen, I'm not putting a guilt chip on people with families and you're getting off work or you're getting off work and you can barely get here and you're rushing.

19:56.494 --> 20:02.802
So you get in the last, you know, at the end or not at the end, but at the

20:02.978 --> 20:05.182
The service already started listening.

20:05.202 --> 20:06.204
We don't take attendance.

20:06.224 --> 20:07.567
We're not sitting there with a stopwatch.

20:08.329 --> 20:09.611
We're not looking at those things.

20:09.631 --> 20:12.336
But I'm just saying, if you can, if you're hungry, you get here.

20:14.100 --> 20:15.242
Because you want to prepare your heart.

20:15.262 --> 20:16.024
You want to say, you know what?

20:16.865 --> 20:19.330
We want to be ready for what the Lord wants to do.

20:19.711 --> 20:21.234
Hungry people lean into worship.

20:22.562 --> 20:24.304
The arms aren't crossed, they're raised in the air.

20:24.644 --> 20:29.329
And I realize some of you are totally new to this and I get the journey aspect of that.

20:29.409 --> 20:31.010
So I'm not trying to be unkind.

20:31.371 --> 20:42.341
I'm just simply saying that the Bible talks repeatedly and we have messages on it you could listen to on the value of raising your hands and what it means to do that and how that will do something.

20:42.381 --> 20:46.826
The Lord will do something through that in your life that will bring victory and blessing to your life.

20:49.408 --> 20:51.250
Hungry people come to the altar

20:51.586 --> 20:56.392
because pride isn't driving them, need is, and a desire for God is.

20:59.255 --> 21:07.845
Hungry people, and this is something hungry people respond quickly because they aren't negotiating with God, they're pursuing God.

21:09.627 --> 21:18.578
So if God's speaking, my heart has heard you say this on the set, come seek me, your heart will I seek?

21:19.682 --> 21:28.651
He doesn't say, well, you know, I've got, I'm a king, you remember that God, and I've got an appointment here, an appointment here, and I've got an army, I've got a manage, and Joey, I'm just driving me crazy.

21:29.271 --> 21:32.174
No, David says, my heart has heard you say, come see me.

21:33.175 --> 21:33.755
Here I come!

21:35.897 --> 21:38.400
Without, that's the mark of a hungry person.

21:38.800 --> 21:40.141
Here's what he says.

21:40.502 --> 21:49.170
One thing I've desired, this is what I'll seek, that I might dwell in the house of the Lord, all the days of my life.

21:49.314 --> 21:51.176
that I might behold the beauty of the Lord.

21:51.577 --> 22:03.670
All of these things, there's this desire to instantaneously move into the presence of God when God is calling to say, I'm in, I'm on, I want it, I'm hungry.

22:06.613 --> 22:13.641
So hunger doesn't just admire the menu, it orders off the menu.

22:13.661 --> 22:14.642
It says, hey,

22:15.042 --> 22:17.765
I'm gonna take you up on that taste and see that the Lord is good.

22:18.406 --> 22:23.471
I'll have one of those, one of those, one of those, one of those, and anything else you wanna give me, I'm gonna eat.

22:24.392 --> 22:26.795
It's that hunger for God.

22:28.457 --> 22:31.920
Let me just wrap this up, three steps to a hungry heart.

22:31.941 --> 22:33.042
Number one, admit your need.

22:34.764 --> 22:38.127
For some of you, there are degrees of hunger.

22:38.748 --> 22:40.490
We all understand that physically.

22:41.231 --> 22:44.274
Sometimes like you're starved, and other times you're like kind of hungry.

22:46.978 --> 22:53.185
For some tonight, the admission would be, I'm not as hungry as I used to be or I should be.

22:56.148 --> 22:57.630
And I don't want to stay that way.

23:00.333 --> 23:03.336
You know, a hungry heart is a person.

23:03.957 --> 23:08.402
A hungry heart a person is a person who's full on for God, who's wholeheartedly seeking God.

23:10.724 --> 23:15.890
If you're not hungry, then what happens is

23:15.970 --> 23:21.436
you really risk being in the place of being half-hearted or lukewarm toward the things of God.

23:23.599 --> 23:24.880
Hungry people are on fire.

23:24.920 --> 23:29.325
They just want anything and everything God has.

23:31.387 --> 23:42.160
So if you're not there and you say, you know, there were days when I was hungrier than I am now to say, God, I am not as hungry as I used to be and you're gonna have to change that in me.

23:42.800 --> 23:44.242
But I'm saying, here I am.

23:44.322 --> 23:45.223
You tell me what to do.

23:45.303 --> 23:47.185
I'll do it.

23:47.205 --> 23:49.288
Number two, return to the table.

23:49.348 --> 23:50.610
Don't wait until you feel it.

23:50.630 --> 23:56.377
Too many feelings won't lead you into depth spiritually.

23:58.679 --> 24:00.321
You have to just say, I'm gonna do it.

24:00.381 --> 24:01.423
I'm gonna worship.

24:01.443 --> 24:02.584
I'm gonna be at the altar.

24:03.065 --> 24:04.666
I'm gonna have my devotional time.

24:05.928 --> 24:14.258
And then to all of us, Lord, increase my capacity to desire you.

24:14.530 --> 24:15.315
hunger for you.

